            <thetext>We publish every release using Cloudflares cdnjs service. The update process was usually pull-request based but is moved to an auto update mechanism which saves them a lot of work and could also save us some work for every upcoming release. Check out the documentation about the auto-update mechanism:
https://github.com/cdnjs/cdnjs#adding-a-new-or-updating-an-existing-library

Also check out the pull reuest for 4.1 which includes some hints on how we could get that done without much effort: https://github.com/cdnjs/cdnjs/pull/4107</thetext>
